				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The triangle channel is never silenced, so playing it at the highest frequencies will make the wave effectively output a flat signal in the middle. This will cause a click almost every time, whereas stopping it won't cause as much. Also, on emulators with imperfect low-pass filtering, you will get awful sounds. I believe Mega Man II uses this technique to silence the triangle, with very clicky results.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

